content.title: More than just the essentials
content.description:
From the second you open your account, get everything you need to do business locally and around the world.

  • Issue physical and virtual cards for you and your team
  • Send transfers around the world with ease
  • Receive money with IBAN and SWIFT/BIC account details
  • Accept payments online or in-person
  • Exchange 25+ currencies at the interbank rate (within allowance, during market hours)

items.title: How do I open a Business account with Revolut Business?
items.description:
Opening a Revolut Business account is quick and easy.

  1. Fill out a short online form — it only takes about 10 minutes.
  2. We’ll review your business account application as part of your business account set-up process.
  3. Once approved, we'll set up your account, and you will be ready to go. It's that simple.

We may need to reach out to confirm a few details or leave you a message on your application, guiding you through the required information or documentation.

items.title: Is Revolut Business a bank?
items.description:
Revolut Business is a bank in most countries we operate in.

Where we don't have our banking license, we offer many of the same features as a bank, and your money is still protected by licensed banks.

Here’s a quick overview:

  • We are a bank in the EEA, where we're authorised by the Bank of Lithuania
  • We don’t yet have a full banking license in the UK
  • We’re not yet a bank in the US, Australia, or Singapore

items.title: Am I eligible for a Revolut Business account?
items.description:
To open a Revolut Business account, the following requirements must be met:
  • Your company must be fully incorporated and active
  • Your company must be registered in an eligible country
  • Your company's legal form should not be a charity, operate in the public sector, act as a cooperative, or be registered as sole traders (all legal forms will be listed for your jurisdiction during signup. If you don't find your legal form listed, unfortunately we cannot support your company at the moment)
  • Your company doesn’t operate in unsupported industries
  • Your current legal home address should be in UK, EEA, Switzerland, Australia, Singapore, or the US.
